                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/658: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-23T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 23, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>335. Your 680, May 18, 2 p.m., Chinese Maritime Customs. If you are asked to
                    advise any Chinese Maritime Customs official in regard to action affecting the
                    deposit in question, you should state that you do not wish to express an opinion
                    in the matter.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Hankow, Peiping, and Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
